cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper deals with scene understanding, 3D reconstruction, and human pose estimation from a single-view image, which are all topics related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of physical commonsense and human-object interaction to improve the performance of the algorithm suggests that it may also fall under the categories of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) for inference suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the estimation of object bounding boxes and room layout, which are topics related to computer graphics (cs.GR).
